                    THE SMELL OF WAR<br><br>
Paul, <br>
You asked about War, here's a slice of life, of war, of the fear of war.<br>
I hated nights in Nam when the moon was her brightest, when the lesser light that rules the night betrayed us. I hated the smell of gooks and the sound their drum beats made at night, I hated fearing fear and the smell of fear. <br><br>
